gomodel:SYNGO_1500  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immuno gold labeling of Kir6.2 channels.\n\nFig.1: \"We first examined the expression of KATP channels in the hippocampus by immunogold labeling of the Kir6.1 (Fig. 1a) and Kir6.2 (Fig. 1b) subunits. Overall, the labeling shows that both Kir6.1 and Kir6.2 proteins are found on synaptic membranes of terminals and spines as well as in vesicular structures within the synaptic cytoplasm. By comparing the labeling patterns between Kir6.1 and Kir6.2 proteins, we found that the Kir6.1 subunits were located predominantly in the pre-synaptic membrane (active zone), whereas Kir6.2 subunit was most likely to be located in the perisynaptic area of the terminals (Fig. 1c and d). These findings indicate that Kir6.1 proteins in the pre-synaptic terminal are concentrated within the synaptic active zone. \". Experimental description: The post-embedding immuno-gold method has been described (Wang et al. 1998; Zhao et al. 1998). In this study, sections from the CA1 stratum radiatum of the hippocampus of three male Sprague)Dawley rats (37-days old) were studied." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1500" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

